Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE Hotels are delighted to offer for sale both the Sea Temple Golf & Country Club and the housing estate development situated in Port Douglas, North Queensland, Australia. The flexibility to acquire one or both of these assets presents an unrivaled opportunity in today's market.

The offering includes:
* An award winning 18 hole golf course and/or the adjoining housing estate development.
* An 18-hole, 6,125m*, Par 71 championship golf course - Thomson, Wolveridge & Perrett design.
* A housing estate development with 45 remaining premium home sites fronting the golf course averaging 820sqm*.
* Existing Development Approval for an additional 10 fairway lots averaging 1,333sqm*.
* Superbly located at the doorstep to the Great Barrier Reef on the beautiful Port Douglas Peninsula

For Sale individually or in one-line by Expressions of Interest, closing Wednesday 14th November 2012 at 4:00pm

To obtain a detailed Information Memorandum contact the Exclusive Agents listed below.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
AN OPPORTUNITY TO BUY THE REMAINING 27 UNITS IN ONE LINE PLUS MANAGEMENT AND LETTING RIGHTS

- Fully serviced 8 year old modern resort including 180m feature swimming pool / lap pools

- 72 units in total over 2 levels including managers office and 94 basement carparks

- 2 & 3 bedroom apartments

- Sell down opportunity

- Strong trading performance

- 15 units for immediate occupation, 12 units not in use requiring repairs and refurbishment

For Sale by Expressions of Interest

CBRE Hotels have been retained exclusively to market the freehold going concern interest in the 4.5 star luxury resort – QT Port Douglas.
 
Key investment considerations include:
•	Offered for sale with vacant possession 
•	Situated on a large 49,350sqm* parcel of land in a prime location 550m* from Four Mile Beach
•	Large scale luxury resort with 127 one and two bedroom villas (169 keys) - 111 apartments plus central facilities, 16 individually owned (strata)
•	Resort facilities include conference/event facilities, restaurant, relaxed cocktail bar, lagoon style swimming pool with a swim up pool bar, day spa, two tennis courts, gymnasium and lap pool
•	Port Douglas is an upmarket resort town renowned as a wedding and conference destination and tourist hot spot, utilised as a base for visits to the world heritage listed Great Barrier Reef and Daintree National Park
•	Largely vacant parcel of land (17,450sqm*) on separate title allowing for additional development or sold off (split lots)
Approx.*

The interest in QT Port Douglas resort including 111 apartments, central facilities, management rights and a large adjoining block of land is offered via an Expression of Interest campaign closing 28th June 2018 at 1:00pm AEST (unless sold prior).
